# Form Protection From Theme Settings

- If the theme provides settings for reCAPTCHA, Cloudflare Turnstile, or any other anti-bot provider, every eligible form must enforce protection according to those settings.
- Do not enable protection on one form and leave others unprotected when global protection is enabled in theme settings.
- Treat protection configuration as centralized behavior, not per-form ad hoc logic.

## Required Enforcement

- Read protection provider, keys, and enable/disable state from theme settings.
- Apply the selected protection provider consistently across all forms (contact, login, register, comment, custom forms, and AJAX forms where applicable).
- If provider is enabled but credentials are missing/invalid, fail safely:
  - block insecure submission where required, and
  - show a clear user-facing message plus admin-facing guidance.
- Server-side verification is mandatory; client-side widgets alone are not sufficient.

## Architecture Requirements

- Use a shared helper/service for provider detection and token verification.
- Avoid duplicating provider logic in templates.
- Keep graceful fallbacks when protection is disabled by settings.
- Keep plugin/service integrations optional and guarded to avoid fatal errors.

## Validation Checklist

- Confirm each form respects the current protection setting.
- Confirm switching provider in settings updates behavior for all forms.
- Confirm disabled protection setting disables challenge behavior consistently.
- Confirm no PHP notices, warnings, JS runtime errors, or broken submissions are introduced.
